    .section.section-dark.section-image
      .container
        .row
          .ml-auto.mr-auto
            h2.title.text-center Frequently asked questions
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title For whom is this course?
            p.description
              | The course is for experienced and motivated engineers who already know how to write good code and get things done. If you want to become an exceptional leader and make a big positive impact on your team and organization. Even though this is not a coding course, you'll learn about software architecture, code reviews, pair programming, and other fundamentally important engineering practices.
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title What are admission requirements for the course?
            p.description The content of the course requires a certain level of maturity. To create an effective learning environment, we invite motivated developers with at least three years of commercial software development experience.
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title I have sufficient IT experience, but I am not a developer. Can I participate?
            p.description Because software development is a team sport, we welcome people with different backgrounds and perspectives – development managers, Scrum Masters, Product Owners, SREs, QA engineers.
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title How is the learning process organized?
            p.description
              | You will work with other developers in a small group. We'll be solving different challenges, such as optimizing the development process, making grumpy colleagues happy, finding cost-effective solutions to problems, refactoring the interviewing process. We'll also address your current career, team, and company challenges.
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title Would I receive a certificate upon completing the course?
            p.description Yes, you will receive a Certificate of Accomplishment.
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title What is the language of instruction?
            p.description The course is taught in English. Non-native speakers are welcome.
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title How would I develop my knowledge after the course?
            p.description
              | You will receive a list of books, blogs, videos for self-development. After the masterclass, you'll stay connected with other alumni and Eduards via group chat.
        .row
          .col-md-6.ml-auto.mr-auto.text-center
            h6.title How do I convince my manager to send me to this course?
            p.description
              | Tell it like it is: Coursera is for beginners, conferences are for fun, and you want to gain some serious and practical skills to bring your team and organization to the next level. After the course, you'll be motivated like never before and bring tons of inspiration back to the workplace. You'll also earn a certificate. If you dislike the course, you'll get your money back. No questions asked.
